column18: because theyâ€™d lost their sense of hope. Jolynn Winter committed suicide on January 8

column20: in northern Ontario. Wapekeka has a population of about 400 and the only access in or out is by plane. The nearest medical care centres are in Sioux Lookout and Thunder Bay â€” 450 km and 600 km away
column22: adults learned that a number of children had created a suicide pact and they immediately asked Health Canada to fund local suicide prevention services. The request was denied. It was an â€œawkward timeâ€ in the funding cycle

column29: an Anglican minister and Boy Scout leader named Ralph Rowe sexually assaulted more than 500 indigenous boys in Northern Ontario
column30: many from Wapekeka. Two years ago
column31: the sole elementary school in Wapekeka burned down. There is no high school; in grade nine
